title: 6 nuns kidnapped from bus in Haiti, Catholic organization says
description: Six Catholic nuns along with others traveling on a bus in Port-au-Prince, Haiti, were kidnapped Friday, a Catholic organization said.

title: Caged woman leads Tel Aviv rally calling for the release of Gaza hostages
description: A woman locked inside a cage was the focal point of a march to Israel's defense ministry buildings in Tel Aviv to press for the release of hostages held in Gaza.

title: Newborn safe after being left in a shopping bag on a freezing street
description: A newborn girl is in hospital after being found wrapped in a towel in a shopping bag on a London street, British police said on Friday as the capital was experiencing sub-zero temperatures.

title: Video shows damaged cemetery after Israeli forces search for hostages in Gaza
description: Israel's military indicated to NBC News that its forces damaged a Khan Younis cemetery in the search for hostages that may have been buried there. Video showed broken graves and uncovered human remains.

title: Video shows doomed Peregrine lunar lander firing thrusters on its way to re-entry
description: Astrobotic Technology's doomed moon lander met a fiery end Thursday, burning up in Earth’s atmosphere to end its mission. Video captured its thrusters being fired over Australia.

title: North Korea says it tested underwater nuclear drone
description: North Korea said it conducted a test of its underwater nuclear weapons system in a protest against joint military drills by South Korea, the U.S. and Japan.

title: Brazil cracks down on illegal gold mining in the Amazon
description: Brazilian officials are carrying out specialized operations to put a clamp on illegal gold mining in the Amazon Rainforest as the race for gold is pushing a group of Indigenous people to the brink of death.

title: 3 people charged with murdering a Hmong American comedian in Colombia
description: Three people have been jailed in the kidnapping and killing of Tou Ger Xiong, a Hmong American comedian and activist who was found dead near Medellín, Colombia, after going out to meet a woman he reportedly met on social media
